          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Bake the sponge"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C conventional (160°C fan). Grease and line a 23 cm round tin. Whisk the eggs and sugar with an electric hand mixer for 8 to 10 minutes until very pale, thick, and tripled in volume. Fold in the flour and lemon juice and zest with a large metal spoon, cutting gently through the mixture. Pour into the tin and bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in the tin for 10 minutes, then turn out and cool completely on a rack."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make the filling and assemble"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Beat the drained ricotta with the icing sugar until smooth. Stir in the chocolate pieces, glace cherries, mixed peel, and vanilla. Slice the cold sponge into three layers. Place the bottom layer cut-side up on a plate and brush with the rum soaking syrup. Spread half the ricotta filling over it. Add the second sponge layer, brush with syrup, spread with the remaining filling, and add the top layer. Press gently. Chill for 2 hours."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cover and decorate"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Brush the outside of the chilled cake with the warm sieved apricot jam. Roll the marzipan thinly and cover the cake, smoothing it down the sides and trimming the base. Chill for 30 minutes. Mix the icing sugar with just enough cold water to make a thick, pourable icing. Pour over the top and ease it down the sides with a palette knife. Decorate with halved glace cherries, mixed peel, and candied fruit before the icing sets."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
